== 人口统计 ==
[[纽约大都会区|纽约大都会区]]拥有[[亚洲|亚洲]]以外的最大的华裔人口，截至2013年，有779,269人<ref>{{cite web|url=http://factfinder2.census.gov/faces/tableservices/jsf/pages/productview.xhtml?pid=ACS_13_1YR_DP05&prodType=table|title=ACS DEMOGRAPHIC AND HOUSING ESTIMATES  2013 American Community Survey 1-Year Estimates New York-Newark-Bridgeport, NY-NJ-CT-PA CSA|publisher=U.S. Census Bureau|accessdate=2014-11-10|archive-date=2014-10-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141008010819/http://factfinder2.census.gov/faces/tableservices/jsf/pages/productview.xhtml?pid=ACS_13_1YR_DP05&prodType=table|dead-url=no}}</ref>，包括至少12个唐人街, 包括6个<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2011/06/24/nyregion/asian-new-yorkers-asian-new-yorkers-seek-power-to-match-surging-numbers.html?scp=1&sq=asians&st=cse |title=Asian New Yorkers Seek Power to Match Numbers |author=Kirk Semple |newspaper=The New York Times |date=2011-06-23 |accessdate=2014-10-03 |archive-date=2021-12-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211203054728/https://www.nytimes.com/2011/06/24/nyregion/asian-new-yorkers-asian-new-yorkers-seek-power-to-match-surging-numbers.html?scp=1&sq=asians&st=cse |dead-url=no }}</ref>（或9个）新兴的唐人街：[[纽约市|纽约市]][[皇后区|皇后区]]的可乐娜和白石<ref name=McGlinn>{{cite journal|url=http://geographyplanning.buffalostate.edu/MSG%202002/13_McGlinn.pdf |title=Beyond Chinatown: Dual Immigration and the Chinese Population of Metropolitan New York City, 2000 |page=4 |author=Lawrence A. McGlinn |journal=Middle States Geographer |year=2002 |volume=35 |issue=1153 |accessdate=2014-10-03 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121029075400/http://geographyplanning.buffalostate.edu/MSG%202002/13_McGlinn.pdf |archivedate=2012-10-29 |df= }}</ref>，曼哈顿的[[东哈莱姆|东哈莱姆]]，一个在[[拿骚县|拿骚县]]，[[长岛|长岛]]; [[新泽西州|新泽西州]]的[[爱迪生_(新泽西州)|爱迪生]]和帕西帕尼-特洛伊山<ref name=McGlinn/> ，更不用说在纽约市大都会地区到处出现的新兴的华裔飞地。

纽约市是全美国[[华人|华人]]最多的城市，2014年估计有573,388人，为中国新移民的主要目的地<ref name=2012ChineseImmigration>{{cite web|url=https://www.dhs.gov/yearbook-immigration-statistics-2012-legal-permanent-residents|title=Yearbook of Immigration Statistics: 2012 Supplemental Table 2|publisher=U.S. Department of Homeland Security|accessdate=2014-03-08|archive-date=2015-06-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150624030947/http://www.dhs.gov/yearbook-immigration-statistics-2012-legal-permanent-residents|dead-url=no}}</ref>。在纽约市的五个区中，毗邻地位于[[长岛|长岛]]西部的[[布鲁克林区|布鲁克林区]]和[[皇后区|皇后区]]，都拥有大量的华人居民，而且增长也最快<ref>{{cite web|url=http://quickfacts.census.gov/qfd/states/36/36047lk.html|title=Kings County (Brooklyn Borough), New York QuickLinks|publisher=U.S. Census Bureau|accessdate=2014-03-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140304220709/http://quickfacts.census.gov/qfd/states/36/36047lk.html|archive-date=2014-03-04|dead-url=yes}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://quickfacts.census.gov/qfd/states/36/36081lk.html|title=Queens County (Queens Borough), New York QuickLinks|publisher=U.S. Census Bureau|accessdate=2014-03-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160225014329/http://quickfacts.census.gov/qfd/states/36/36081lk.html|archive-date=2016-02-25|dead-url=yes}}</ref> 。皇后区和布鲁克林区的华人数量已经在美国所有城市中，仅次于纽约市本身。

== 历史 ==
[[华人|华人]]在纽约市定居，已有相对较长的历史。第一个[[中国|中国]]移民在1870年左右来到[[曼哈顿下城|曼哈顿下城]]，寻找美国提供的黄金机会<ref name="historychinatown">{{cite web|url=http://www.ny.com/articles/chinatown.html|title=The History of New York's Chinatown|last=Waxman|first=Sarah|publisher=ny.com|accessdate=2014-10-03|archive-date=2017-05-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170525014333/https://www.ny.com/articles/chinatown.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。到1880年，五点一带的华人区估计有200到多达1,100名华人<ref name=historychinatown/>。

然而，1882年生效的[[美国排华法案|美国排华法案]]，造成了移民到纽约和美国其他地区的华人数量的急剧下降<ref name=historychinatown />。后来，1943年，中国人被给予了少量的移民配额，社区人口逐渐增加，到1968年，美国华人人口迅速增加<ref name=historychinatown />。在过去几年中，主宰唐人街几十年的[[粤语|粤语]]的地位，正迅速被大部分中国新移民的[[通用语|通用语]][[普通话|普通话]]所取代<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2009/10/22/nyregion/22chinese.html |title=In Chinatown, Sound of the Future Is Mandarin |date=2009-10-21 |accessdate=2011-06-29 |work=The New York Times |first=Kirk |last=Semple |archive-date=2011-07-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110714084739/http://www.nytimes.com/2009/10/22/nyregion/22chinese.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

