[[法拉盛|法拉盛]]是[[亚洲|亚洲]]以外，以及纽约市内，最大和发展最快的[[唐人街|唐人街]]之一。法拉盛华埠<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=5PSYZMs8TzEC&pg=PA237&lpg=PA237&dq=fort+lee+koreatown+pyong+min#v=onepage&q&f=false|title=Asian Americans: Contemporary Trends and Issues Second Edition, Edited by Pyong Gap Min|publisher=Pine Forge Press - An Imprint of Sage Publications, Inc.|year=2006|accessdate=2010-11-08|isbn=978-1-4129-0556-5}}</ref>位于缅街（Main Street）及其以西地区，特别是沿着罗斯福大道（Roosevelt Avenue）的地段，已经成为法拉盛华埠的主要枢纽。然而，法拉盛华埠继续沿着凯辛娜大道向东南延伸，并向北越过了北大道（Northern Boulevard）。

===历史===
====早期====
1645年，根据[[荷兰西印度公司|荷兰西印度公司]]的宪章，[[荷兰|荷兰]]殖民者在法拉盛河东岸建立了法拉盛，为[[新尼德兰|新尼德兰]]殖民地的一部分。该镇以[[荷兰|荷兰]]西南部城市，该公司的主要港口[[弗利辛恩|弗利辛恩]]命名；法拉盛则是这个城镇的荷兰语名字的[[盎格鲁化|盎格鲁化]]。

1664年，英国人控制了[[新阿姆斯特丹|新阿姆斯特丹]]，结束了荷兰对殖民地的控制，并重新命名为[[英属纽约省|英属纽约省]]。当皇后县于1683年成立时，法拉盛镇就是组成该县最初的五个镇之一<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bklyn-genealogy-info.com/Map/5.Bor.Q.Rich.html |title=Before the Five Borough City:Queens |accessdate=2017-01-19 |archive-date=2009-07-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090703114614/http://www.bklyn-genealogy-info.com/Map/5.Bor.Q.Rich.html |dead-url=no }} This later map shows former boundaries of the Town of Flushing. The map does not show the towns that were part of Queens and are now part of Nassau.</ref>。

====小台北====
在1970年代之前，广东移民一直占据纽约市的华人移民的绝大多数；但是在1970年代，第一波说普通话而不是粤语的华人移民——台湾移民到达纽约市。由于[[曼哈顿华埠|曼哈顿华埠]]由操粵語的工人阶级的粵籍移民所主导，再加上曼哈頓的居住條件擁擠，學歷、經濟及社會地位较高的台籍移民没有选择曼哈顿华埠，而选择在法拉盛定居。随着台湾人口的增长，法拉盛唐人街创造了更高的[[生活水平|生活水平]]和更好的住房条件。

台湾移民在以[[白种人|白种人]]为主的法拉盛建立了立足点。这次来自[[台湾|台湾]]的移民潮，是第一批到达法拉盛的华人。因此它被称为“小台北”或“小台湾”。许多来到法拉盛的移民，是被[[中国共产党|中国共产党]]击败，撤退到台湾的[[国民党|国民党]]的支持者以及军人的后代。与此同时，除了来自台湾的移民，大批[[韩国|韩国]]移民也在法拉盛安家。

====国语區====
多年来，来自不同地区和中国各省的许多非粤语华裔新移民陆续抵达纽约市。这导致另外形成了一个“国语埠”（Mandarin Town），逐渐取代了“小台北”。这波移民操国语和其他中国方言。和台湾人一样，他们也在屬粵語區的曼哈顿唐人街面临語言及文化上的溝通障礙，因此定居在法拉盛以及艾浒（Elmhurst）。法拉盛的华人在几十年里变得非常多样化，因为来自不同省份的人们开始到达，将不同的语言和文化特征融入到唐人街<ref name="Foner">{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=MR4iVnvulMQC&pg=PA158#v=onepage&q=&f=false|title=New immigrants in New York|author=Nancy Foner|publisher=[[Columbia_University_Press|Columbia University Press]]|year=2001|pages=158–161|isbn=978-0-231-12414-0|access-date=2017-01-19|archive-date=2015-02-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150222105455/http://books.google.com/books?id=MR4iVnvulMQC&pg=PA158#v=onepage&q=&f=false|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=5PSYZMs8TzEC&pg=PA134&dq=Flushing+Chinatown+Little+Taiwan&hl=en&ei=-2xaTtqbFY7PgAej1q2zDA&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=7&ved=0CEYQ6AEwBg#v=onepage&q=Flushing%20Chinatown%20Little%20Taiwan&f=false |title=Asian Americans: contemporary trends ... - Google Books |publisher=Books.google.com |date= |accessdate=2011-08-28 |archive-date=2014-06-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140629200212/http://books.google.com/books?id=5PSYZMs8TzEC&pg=PA134&dq=Flushing+Chinatown+Little+Taiwan&hl=en&ei=-2xaTtqbFY7PgAej1q2zDA&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=7&ved=0CEYQ6AEwBg#v=onepage&q=Flushing%20Chinatown%20Little%20Taiwan&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ZcBxKK0cljcC&pg=PA190&dq=Flushing+Chinatown+Little+Taiwan&hl=en&ei=-2xaTtqbFY7PgAej1q2zDA&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=1&ved=0CCoQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=Flushing%20Chinatown%20Little%20Taiwan&f=false |title=Chinatown: The Socioeconomic ... - Google Books |publisher=Books.google.com |date=1995-01-24 |accessdate=2011-08-28 |archive-date=2014-06-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140629200208/http://books.google.com/books?id=ZcBxKK0cljcC&pg=PA190&dq=Flushing+Chinatown+Little+Taiwan&hl=en&ei=-2xaTtqbFY7PgAej1q2zDA&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=1&ved=0CCoQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=Flushing%20Chinatown%20Little%20Taiwan&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=NagJFMxtkAcC&pg=PA104&dq=Flushing+Chinatown+Little+Taiwan&hl=en&ei=tHBaTpiYAeWt0AHsrrCTCQ&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=1&ved=0CCkQ6AEwADgK#v=onepage&q=Flushing%20Chinatown%20Little%20Taiwan&f=false |title=Still the golden door: the Third ... - Google Books |publisher=Books.google.com |author=David M. Reimers |accessdate=2011-12-15 |archive-date=2013-01-31 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130131083831/http://books.google.com/books?id=NagJFMxtkAcC&pg=PA104&dq=Flushing+Chinatown+Little+Taiwan&hl=en&ei=tHBaTpiYAeWt0AHsrrCTCQ&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=1&ved=0CCkQ6AEwADgK#v=onepage&q=Flushing%20Chinatown%20Little%20Taiwan&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

法拉盛及其唐人街毗邻着同样快速增长的长岛韩国城<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=5PSYZMs8TzEC&pg=PA237&lpg=PA237&dq=fort+lee+koreatown+pyong+min#v=onepage&q&f=false|title=Asian Americans: Contemporary Trends and Issues Second Edition, Edited by Pyong Gap Min|publisher=Pine Forge Press - An Imprint of Sage Publications, Inc|year=2006|accessdate=2013-01-11|isbn=9781412905565}}</ref>。

===华人人口统计===
缅街和罗斯福大道的交汇处是法拉盛的商业中心，在社区的最西部边缘，集中了大量的中国和韩国企业，包括亚洲餐馆。华人企业尤其主导了缅街及其西边的街区。该地区商店的大部分标志和广告已使用中文。华人占亚洲人口和法拉盛人口的比例越来越大。因此，法拉盛华埠已经增长到成为亚洲以外的第二大唐人街。事实上，法拉盛唐人街可能会在几年内超越原来的曼哈顿唐人街本身。<ref name="Foner2">{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=MR4iVnvulMQC&pg=PA158#v=onepage&q=&f=false |title=New immigrants in New York |first=Nancy |last=Foner |publisher=[[Columbia_University_Press|Columbia University Press]] |location=New York |year=2001 |pages=158–161 |isbn=978-0-231-12414-0 |access-date=2017-01-19 |archive-date=2015-02-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150222105455/http://books.google.com/books?id=MR4iVnvulMQC&pg=PA158#v=onepage&q=&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Zhou">{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ghKia5k6hXUC&pg=PA57#v=onepage&q=&f=false |title=Contemporary Chinese America: Immigration, Ethnicity, and Community |author=Min Zhou |publisher=Temple University Press |location=Philadelphia |year=2009 |pages=57–59 |isbn=978-1-59213-858-6 |access-date=2017-01-19 |archive-date=2015-02-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150222120050/http://books.google.com/books?id=ghKia5k6hXUC&pg=PA57#v=onepage&q=&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Montefinise">{{cite news |url=http://www.queenstribune.com/anniversary2002/koreans.htm |title=Koreans In Queens: Finding A Second Home In The Borough Of Queens |first=Angela |last=Montefinise |newspaper=[[Queens_Tribune|Queens Tribune]] |year=2002 |accessdate=2010-09-04 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100728074644/http://www.queenstribune.com/anniversary2002/koreans.htm |archivedate=2010年7月28日 |df= }}</ref>

法拉盛华人商会1986年估计，法拉盛约有6万华人。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://qcpages.qc.edu/Asian_American_Center/research_papers/aacre15.html|accessdate=2010-03-29|title=Chinese in Chinatown and Flushing|author=Hsiang-shui Chen|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110720033810/http://qcpages.qc.edu/Asian_American_Center/research_papers/aacre15.html|archivedate=2011-07-20}}</ref>1990年，亚裔占法拉盛核心区人口的41％，华人又占亚裔的41％。<ref name="Foner"/> 并且，华人在亚裔以及法拉盛及其唐人街的总人口中占越来越大的比例。来自[[中国大陆|中国大陆]]的合法<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dhs.gov/files/statistics/publications/LPR11.shtm|title=Yearbook of Immigration Statistics: 2011 Supplemental Table 2|publisher=U.S. Department of Homeland Security|accessdate=2012-09-18|archive-date=2012-08-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120808080130/http://www.dhs.gov/files/statistics/publications/LPR11.shtm|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dhs.gov/files/statistics/publications/LPR10.shtm|title=Yearbook of Immigration Statistics: 2010 Supplemental Table 2|publisher=U.S. Department of Homeland Security|accessdate=2012-09-18|archive-date=2012-07-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120712200141/https://www.dhs.gov/files/statistics/publications/LPR10.shtm|dead-url=no}}</ref>和非法移民<ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.nydailynews.com/2011-05-09/news/29541916_1_illegal-chinese-immigrants-qm2-queen-mary|title=Malaysian man smuggled illegal Chinese immigrants into Brooklyn using Queen Mary 2: authorities|author=John Marzulli|publisher=© Copyright 2012 NY Daily News.com|date=2011-05-09|accessdate=2012-09-18|location=New York|archive-date=2015-05-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150505034445/http://www.nydailynews.com/news/world/malaysian-man-smuggled-illegal-chinese-immigrants-brooklyn-queen-mary-2-authorities-article-1.143516|dead-url=no}}</ref>的高比率，持续刺激在法拉盛的华人的增长，如同纽约的所有唐人街一样。

根据《[[纽约每日新闻|纽约每日新闻]]》的文章，法拉盛的唐人街作为纽约市第二大华人社区，拥有33,526名华人，从17,363人，已经增长了93％。[[布鲁克林華埠|布鲁克林華埠]]现在则排名第一，成为纽约的最大的唐人街，有34,218名华人，比起2000年的19,963人，增加了71％。至于曼哈顿的唐人街，其华裔人口从2000年的34,554人下降到28,681人，排名第3位，下降了17％。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/changing-chinatowns-move-manhattan-sunset-park-home-chinese-nyc-article-1.948028|title=The changing Chinatowns: Move over Manhattan, Sunset Park now home to most Chinese in NYC|author=Daniel Beekman|newspaper=NY Daily News|date=2011-08-05|accessdate=2012-09-18|archive-date=2011-12-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111211114045/http://www.nydailynews.com/changing-chinatowns-move-manhattan-sunset-park-home-chinese-nyc-article-1.948028|dead-url=no}}</ref>

{{Wide image|Flushing Queens May 2015 2.jpg|800px|3=<div align=center>[[纽约|纽约]]法拉盛华埠, 世界上最大的唐人街。法拉盛华埠，缅街、凯辛娜大道和41大道的交汇处。2016年，[[皇后區|皇后區]]快速增长的华人接近25万，<ref>{{cite web|url=https://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/ACS/16_1YR/S0201/0500000US36081/popgroup~016|title=Selected Population Profile in the United States - 2016 American Community Survey 1-Year Estimates Queens County, New York Chinese alone|publisher=United States Census Bureau|accessdate=November 26, 2017|archive-url=https://archive.today/20200214004137/https://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/ACS/16_1YR/S0201/0500000US36081/popgroup~016|archive-date=2020-02-14|dead-url=yes}}</ref>居除纽约市以外的美国各城市第一名。</div>|dir=rtl}}

===文化===
法拉盛现在与曼哈顿的唐人街竞争，成为中国文化的中心，<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2009/10/22/nyregion/22chinese.html|title=In Chinatown, Sound of the Future Is Mandarin|date=2009-10-21|accessdate=2010-04-06|work=The New York Times|first=Kirk|last=Semple|archive-date=2011-07-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110714084739/http://www.nytimes.com/2009/10/22/nyregion/22chinese.html|dead-url=no}}</ref> 被称为“中国曼哈顿”。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2014/10/05/realestate/downtown-flushing-where-asian-cultures-thrive.html?contentCollection=realestate&action=click&module=NextInCollection&region=Footer&pgtype=article|title=Downtown Flushing: Where Asian Cultures Thrive|author=Vera Haller|newspaper=The New York Times|date=2014-10-01|accessdate=2014-10-02|archive-date=2021-09-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210909154513/https://www.nytimes.com/2014/10/05/realestate/downtown-flushing-where-asian-cultures-thrive.html?contentCollection=realestate&action=click&module=NextInCollection&region=Footer&pgtype=article|dead-url=no}}</ref> 一年一度的[[春节|春节]]游行，规模越来越大。在法拉盛,开设了越来越多的中国超市，出售多种多样且独特的中国食品和配料，其中最大的包括[[香港超级市场|香港超级市场]]和纽约超市，华人连锁超市也在迅速成长。<ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=_4QcI7q4CG0C&pg=PA97&dq=Hong+Kong+Supermarket+Flushing&hl=en&ei=UXrSTs3NMobh0QGx3rUn&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=4&ved=0CEsQ6AEwAw#v=onepage&q=Hong%20Kong%20Supermarket%20Flushing&f=false |title=Queens: what to do, where to go (and ... - Ellen Freudenheim - Google Books |publisher=Books.google.com |accessdate=2011-12-15 |archive-date=2014-06-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140629091452/http://books.google.com/books?id=_4QcI7q4CG0C&pg=PA97&dq=Hong+Kong+Supermarket+Flushing&hl=en&ei=UXrSTs3NMobh0QGx3rUn&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=4&ved=0CEsQ6AEwAw#v=onepage&q=Hong%20Kong%20Supermarket%20Flushing&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=YjJSI1L5QCQC&pg=PA79&dq=Hong+Kong+Supermarket+Flushing&hl=en&ei=UXrSTs3NMobh0QGx3rUn&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=2&ved=0CEMQ6AEwAQ#v=onepage&q=Hong%20Kong%20Supermarket%20Flushing&f=false |title=Nosh New York: The Food Lover's ... - Myra Alperson - Google Books |publisher=Books.google.com |date= |accessdate=2011-11-29 |archive-date=2014-01-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140107171941/http://books.google.com/books?id=YjJSI1L5QCQC&pg=PA79&dq=Hong+Kong+Supermarket+Flushing&hl=en&ei=UXrSTs3NMobh0QGx3rUn&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=2&ved=0CEMQ6AEwAQ#v=onepage&q=Hong%20Kong%20Supermarket%20Flushing&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Greenhouse |first=Steven |url=http://cityroom.blogs.nytimes.com/2008/12/09/supermarket-to-pay-back-wages-and-overtime/ |title=Supermarket to Pay Back Wages and Overtime - NYTimes.com |publisher=Cityroom.blogs.nytimes.com |date=2008-12-09 |accessdate=2011-11-29 |archive-date=2011-11-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111101064539/http://cityroom.blogs.nytimes.com/2008/12/09/supermarket-to-pay-back-wages-and-overtime/ |dead-url=no }}</ref> 法拉盛作为在亚洲之外中国文化的中心崛起，归因于美国华人显著的多样性。

====语言====
[[普通话|普通话]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2009/10/22/nyregion/22chinese.html|title=In Chinatown, Sound of the Future Is Mandarin|date=2009-10-21|accessdate=2011-07-16|work=The New York Times|first=Kirk|last=Semple|archive-date=2011-07-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110714084739/http://www.nytimes.com/2009/10/22/nyregion/22chinese.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>（包括[[北京方言|北京方言]]、东北话）、[[闽语|闽语]]（包括[[闽東话|闽東话]]、[[莆田话|莆田话]]、[[闽南话|闽南话]]）、[[吴语|吴语]]（[[上海话|上海话]]、[[苏州话|苏州话]]、[[杭州话|杭州话]]、[[温州话|温州话]]）、[[粤语|粤语]]和英语，在法拉盛唐人街都普遍使用，而[[客家话|客家话]]和[[蒙古语|蒙古语]]现在也出现。

====美食====
[[中国菜|中国菜]]的流行风格在法拉盛无处不在，<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2008/07/30/dining/30flushing.html|title=Let the Meals Begin: Finding Beijing in Flushing|author=Julia Moskin|work=The New York Times|date=2008-07-30|accessdate=2011-06-26|archive-date=2011-08-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110829063830/http://www.nytimes.com/2008/07/30/dining/30flushing.html|dead-url=no}}</ref> 包括[[客家菜|客家菜]]、[[臺湾菜|臺湾菜]]、[[上海菜|上海菜]]、[[湘菜|湘菜]]、[[川菜|川菜]]、[[粤菜|粤菜]]、[[闽菜|闽菜]]、[[新疆菜|新疆菜]]、[[浙菜|浙菜]]以及韩国中华料理。甚至相对冷门的东北菜, 以及蒙古美食，现在可以在法拉盛找到。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2010/02/10/dining/10chine.html?scp=1&sq=dongbei%20cuisine&st=cse|title=Northeast China Branches Out in Flushing|date=2010-02-09|accessdate=2011-05-09|work=The New York Times|first=Julia|last=Moskin|archive-date=2013-11-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131113094952/http://www.nytimes.com/2010/02/10/dining/10chine.html?scp=1&sq=dongbei%20cuisine&st=cse|dead-url=no}}</ref>

====媒体====
《[[北美世界日报|北美世界日报]]》是中国以外最大的中文报纸之一，总部设在皇后区的白石，在法拉盛也设有办事处。<ref name="WJHQ"/>许多其他中文报纸例如《[[中国报|中国报]]》、《[[星岛日报|星岛日报]]》、《[[大纪元时报|大纪元时报]]》，以及其他英文出版物，在法拉盛都能得到。

===公共机构和服务===
[[File:QPL_Flushing_jeh.JPG|thumb]]法拉盛分馆]]
[[皇后图书馆|皇后图书馆]]最大的法拉盛分馆位于凯辛娜大道和缅街的交叉点。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.queenslibrary.org/index.aspx?section_id=12&page_id=44&branch_id=F|title=Flushing|publisher=[[Queens_Library|Queens Library]]|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120223035208/http://queenslibrary.org/index.aspx?page_id=44&section_id=12&branch_id=F|archivedate=2012-02-23}}</ref> 该图书馆设有一个用于公共活动的礼堂。

纽约医院皇后区（New York Hospital Queens）是纽约长老会保健系统的成员，是一个主要的医疗中心，为法拉盛及周边社区提供全面的医疗护理服务。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nyhq.org/|title=New York Hospital Queens|accessdate=2010-04-16|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100619225512/http://nyhq.org/|archivedate=2010-06-19}}</ref> 很多三级医疗诊所也为法拉盛的居民服务。

在法拉盛可以获得各种各样的社会服务，旨在帮助新老中国移民。<ref>{{cite web|url=https://a069-webapps3.nyc.gov/dsial/Agency_Detail.aspx?id=196|title=Chinese Immigrants Services, Inc.|accessdate=2010-04-07|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100527150443/https://a069-webapps3.nyc.gov/dsial/Agency_Detail.aspx?id=196|archivedate=2010-05-27}}</ref>

===交通===
[[纽约市地铁|纽约市地铁]][[IRT法拉盛线|IRT法拉盛线]]的[[法拉盛-缅街车站_(IRT法拉盛线)|法拉盛-缅街车站]]位于缅街和罗斯福大道的交叉点，是法拉盛华埠的心脏，纽约市第三繁忙的十字路口，仅次于曼哈顿的[[时报广场|时报广场]]和[[先驱广场|先驱广场]]。这是皇后区最繁忙的地铁站。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mta.info/nyct/facts/ffsubway.htm#stations|title=The Ten Busiest Subway Stations 2010|publisher=[[Metropolitan_Transportation_Authority|Metropolitan Transportation Authority]]|accessdate=2013-10-27|archive-date=2013-02-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130211062932/http://www.mta.info/nyct/facts/ffsubway.htm#stations|dead-url=no}}</ref> 在缅街/罗斯福大道的交叉点还有许多公共巴士和铁路连接服务唐人街，包括22路巴士以及[[长岛铁路|长岛铁路]]的支线<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mta.info/nyct/service/sevenlin.htm|title=MTA/New York City Transit Subway Line Information - Flushing-Main Street/Roosevelt Avenue|accessdate=2010-04-15|archive-date=2013-04-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130424071140/http://www.mta.info/nyct/service/sevenlin.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>。法拉盛华埠从几条主要高速公路很容易到达，与纽约市和长岛的其他唐人街之间有穿梭巴士来往。

===政治===
[[File:Tuidang_Center_in_Flushing,_NY.JPG|thumb]]
法拉盛唐人街的政治地位似乎显着增加。[[台湾|台湾]]出生的[[劉醇逸|劉醇逸]]，曾任纽约市议员，代表20区，包括法拉盛唐人街和皇后区其他北部社区，在2009年11月当选为纽约市主计长。同时，出生于[[中国|中国]][[上海|上海]]的[[顧雅明|顧雅明]]当选，继承刘醇逸的议员席位。

==卫星唐人街==
===艾浒唐人街===

{{main|埃姆赫斯特 (纽约)}}

[[File:Bwy_Elmhurst_Chinatown_jeh.jpg|thumb]]
迅速成长的艾浒（Elmhurst）唐人街<ref>{{cite web|url=http://queens.about.com/od/photogalleries/ig/Photos-of-Elmhurst/Elmhurst-Chinatown-.htm|title=A Growing Chinatown in Elmhurst|accessdate=2010-10-01|archive-date=2014-07-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140711032947/http://queens.about.com/od/photogalleries/ig/Photos-of-Elmhurst/Elmhurst-Chinatown-.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>是皇后区继法拉盛唐人街之后新开发的第二个唐人街。从前开设中国商店的区域很小，只包括81街和康沃尔大道之间的百老汇，但是现在已扩大到45大道和惠特尼大道，正在发展成法拉盛唐人街的卫星唐人街。该地区还有许多[[东南亚|东南亚]]的商业和商店，包括[[马来西亚华人|马来西亚华人]]，[[新加坡华人|新加坡华人]]，[[印度尼西亚人|印度尼西亚人]]（包括[[印尼華裔|印尼華裔]]），[[泰国人|泰国人]]（包括[[泰國華裔|泰國華裔]]）和[[越南人|越南人]]（包括[[越南華裔|越南華裔]]）的商业。[[香港超级市场|香港超级市场]]和纽约超市作为艾浒唐人街最大的中国超市，销售不同的食品品种<ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=YjJSI1L5QCQC&pg=PA79&dq=Hong+Kong+Supermarket+Flushing&hl=en&ei=UXrSTs3NMobh0QGx3rUn&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=2&ved=0CEMQ6AEwAQ#v=onepage&q=Hong%20Kong%20Supermarket%20Flushing&f=false|title=Nosh New York|publisher=|accessdate=12 April 2016|archive-date=2014-01-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140107171941/http://books.google.com/books?id=YjJSI1L5QCQC&pg=PA79&dq=Hong+Kong+Supermarket+Flushing&hl=en&ei=UXrSTs3NMobh0QGx3rUn&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=2&ved=0CEMQ6AEwAQ#v=onepage&q=Hong%20Kong%20Supermarket%20Flushing&f=false|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=http://cityroom.blogs.nytimes.com/2008/12/09/supermarket-to-pay-back-wages-and-overtime/ | work=The New York Times | first=Steven | last=Greenhouse | title=Supermarket to Pay Back Wages and Overtime | date=2008-12-09 | accessdate=2017-01-19 | archive-date=2011-11-01 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111101064539/http://cityroom.blogs.nytimes.com/2008/12/09/supermarket-to-pay-back-wages-and-overtime/ | dead-url=no }}</ref>。到目前为止，[[国泰银行|国泰银行]]（前亚洲银行）作为唯一的中国银行和这个繁荣的唐人街的主要金融资源，虽然[[汇丰银行|汇丰银行]]、[[美国大通银行|美国大通银行]]和其他银行也位于艾浒的百老汇。如同法拉盛的唐人街，艾浒也有非常高的人口比例说普通话，虽然也有许多人说客家话等其他语言。

===可乐娜===
艾浒唐人街的附属部分是可乐娜（Corona）社区，一个新兴唐人街，在地理上连接法拉盛和艾浒两个较大的唐人街<ref>{{cite web|url=http://geographyplanning.buffalostate.edu/MSG%202002/13_McGlinn.pdf |title=Beyond Chinatown: Dual Immigration and the Chinese Population of Metropolitan New York City, 2000, Page 4 |author=Lawrence A. McGlinn, Department of Geography SUNY-New Paltz |publisher=Middle States Geographer, 2002, 35: 110–119, Journal of the Middle States Division of the Association of American Geographers |accessdate=2013-03-19 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121029075400/http://geographyplanning.buffalostate.edu/MSG%202002/13_McGlinn.pdf |archivedate=2012-10-29 |df= }}</ref>。

===白石===
[[File:World_Journal_Whitestone_jeh.JPG|thumb]]》]]
自2000年以来，成千上万的美国华人迁居到白石，使邻近的法拉盛唐人街达到相当规模，并继续向东扩展，不仅在皇后区区内，还进入了毗邻的[[長島|長島]]上的[[拿骚县|拿骚县]]<ref name=worldjournal/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.forbes.com/sites/hengshao/2014/04/10/chinese-real-estate-buyers-fan-out-to-long-islands-north-shore/|title=Join The Great Gatsby: Chinese Real Estate Buyers Fan Out To Long Island's North Shore|author=Heng Shao|publisher=Forbes|date=2014-04-10|accessdate=2014-10-03|archive-date=2014-10-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141007010651/http://www.forbes.com/sites/hengshao/2014/04/10/chinese-real-estate-buyers-fan-out-to-long-islands-north-shore/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.reuters.com/article/2014/04/25/us-realestate-china-manhattan-insight-idUSBREA3O0TL20140425|title=The Chinese take Manhattan: replace Russians as top apartment buyers|author=Michelle Conlin and Maggie Lu Yueyang|publisher=Thomson Reuters|date=2014-04-25|accessdate=2014-11-28|archive-date=2014-12-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141205110902/http://www.reuters.com/article/2014/04/25/us-realestate-china-manhattan-insight-idUSBREA3O0TL20140425|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

